&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM UNTIL 31 MARCH 2022 TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit an enthusiastic and experienced therapist to work with children, young people and families referred to the primary mental health service. The post holder will join a busy team of primary mental health workers. You will be part of developing a service delivery model, to meet the needs of children and young people referred under Part 1 of the Measure, and to meet the targets for assessment and intervention (Mental Health Wales Measure, 2010).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary mental health service is part of the Child Development and Health Psychology Department. Regular supervision, joint working and training are key aspects of the service. As well as support and supervision within the service the post holder will be able to access appropriate professional support within Cardiff and Vale UHB.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will contribute to the services provided for children, young people and their families with regard to assessment, treatment and consultation on child development, behaviour, mental health and emotional wellbeing. You will be involved in service initiatives, take a role in enhancing multi-disciplinary/multi-agency team work and developing links with the wider network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Quatermass&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;richard.quatermass@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
